# Cloudflare Pages redirects file
# Replaces the "redirects" block from vercel.json
# Format: source  destination  status_code
# Cloudflare Pages natively handles clean URLs and .html stripping,
# so the vercel.json "rewrites" block is not needed here.
#
# WS-AUDIT-004 NOTE (2026-05-06) — DO NOT "FIX" THE 308→200 CHAIN.
# CF Pages canonicalises directory URLs to trailing-slash form (e.g.
# `/products` → 308 → `/products/`) BEFORE the _redirects engine evaluates.
# After the 308, the trailing-slash URL hits the 200-rewrite below and
# serves the index.html. This one-hop 308→200 chain is the standard CF Pages
# behaviour for directories that contain an index.html — it is harmless,
# adds ~5ms, and is NOT a bug. Previous PRs (#148/#149) tried to remove
# either side and triggered ERR_TOO_MANY_REDIRECTS in production. Leave
# the rules below as they are unless the canonicalisation behaviour itself
# changes upstream.

# www → apex 301 redirect (DEF-008)
# Layer 1: Cloudflare Dashboard > DNS > CNAME www → crowagent.ai (CF Pages
# automatically 301-redirects the www custom domain to the apex). Layer 2:
# Cloudflare Rules > Redirect Rules (Match host = www.crowagent.ai → 301
# concat("https://crowagent.ai", http.request.uri.path)). Layer 3 (this file —
# defense in depth): pages-level _redirects splat. Single direction only;
# no apex→www counterpart configured anywhere, so loops are not possible.
https://www.crowagent.ai/*  https://crowagent.ai/:splat  301!

# Directory rewrites — RESTORED 2026-05-06 11:35 UTC (DEF-LOOP-001).
# The earlier removal (WEB-AUDIT-001..010 in PR #148) inverted the actual root
# cause: without these 200-rewrites, CF Pages bidirectional 308-bounces
# `/foo` ↔ `/foo/` (real-world ERR_TOO_MANY_REDIRECTS observed on prod after
# PR #148 merged). Each route has a corresponding /:slug/index.html on disk.
/products                                    /products/index.html                          200
/products/                                   /products/index.html                          200
/blog                                        /blog/index.html                              200
/blog/                                       /blog/index.html                              200
/glossary                                    /glossary/index.html                          200
/glossary/                                   /glossary/index.html                          200
/intel/cyber-essentials-tracker              /intel/cyber-essentials-tracker/index.html    200
/intel/cyber-essentials-tracker/             /intel/cyber-essentials-tracker/index.html    200
/intel/mees-tracker                          /intel/mees-tracker/index.html                200
/intel/mees-tracker/                         /intel/mees-tracker/index.html                200

# Nested tool pages currently request relative assets from /tools/:tool/.
# Serve the root static assets so methodology pages do not receive HTML/404 MIME responses.
/tools/:tool/styles.min.css   /styles.min.css   200
/tools/:tool/scripts.min.js   /scripts.min.js   200
/tools/:tool/chatbot.js       /chatbot.js       200
/tools/:tool/print.css        /print.css        200

